contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:09.896 --> 01:11.012
Uh, hi.

01:11.014 --> 01:13.532
I'm a new patient.

01:13.534 --> 01:16.451
Sign everything.

01:16.453 --> 01:18.320
And bring back my pen.

01:18.322 --> 01:20.322
Thanks.

01:24.160 --> 01:26.545
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:28.864 --> 01:30.832
Nice to see
a friendly face here.

01:30.834 --> 01:32.634
Oh.

01:32.636 --> 01:34.303
A lot of paperwork.

01:34.305 --> 01:35.671
Yes.

01:35.673 --> 01:37.472
Yeah.

01:37.474 --> 01:39.174
You an oxy guy?

01:39.176 --> 01:42.144
You look like an oxy guy.

01:42.146 --> 01:43.228
Uh, no.

01:43.230 --> 01:44.563
Actually, I had brain surgery.

01:44.565 --> 01:47.182
Cool, cool, cool.

01:47.184 --> 01:48.817
I was in a car accident.

01:48.819 --> 01:51.153
I'm an oxy guy.

01:51.155 --> 01:54.573
Okay.

01:54.575 --> 01:57.693
[Clipboard clatters] Hey.

01:57.695 --> 02:00.078
Pen.

02:00.080 --> 02:01.730
Right.

02:01.732 --> 02:04.700
Sorry. Thanks.

02:07.903 --> 02:09.955
[Groans]

02:11.907 --> 02:13.908
[Pills rattle]

02:25.355 --> 02:27.022
So when you're in Manhattan,

02:27.024 --> 02:30.359
would you stop by balthazar
and pick up some croissants?

02:30.361 --> 02:31.760
These aren't any good?

02:31.762 --> 02:33.261
No, they're good.

02:33.263 --> 02:35.480
Why settle for good when
you can have amazing though?

02:35.482 --> 02:37.065
I'll see what I can do.

02:37.067 --> 02:38.650
- But no promises.
- Mmhmm.

02:38.652 --> 02:40.769
The Van Der Gelts are
returning from Chiang Mai,

02:40.771 --> 02:42.988
and they need the Garuda
in their mansion.

02:42.990 --> 02:45.607
Between Hank's doctor-speak
and your art-speak,

02:45.609 --> 02:47.709
I have no idea
what anyone's saying anymore.

02:47.711 --> 02:49.127
[Chuckles]

02:49.129 --> 02:50.712
The Van Der Gelts
are important collectors.

02:50.714 --> 02:51.780
Okay.

02:51.782 --> 02:53.999
Chiang Mai is a city
in Thailand.

02:54.001 --> 02:55.834
The Garuda is
this huge sculpture they bought,

02:55.836 --> 02:59.287
and a mansion is
a big, fancy house.

02:59.289 --> 03:01.807
Thank you for that.

03:01.809 --> 03:04.509
So, uh, any weekend plans?

03:04.511 --> 03:06.561
No. Why?

03:06.563 --> 03:08.463
Don't do this.

03:08.465 --> 03:10.599
- Do what?
- Please don't do this.

03:10.601 --> 03:12.267
I'm not doing anything.

03:12.269 --> 03:13.902
You're literally ripping
my heart out.

03:13.904 --> 03:16.104
[Laughs] Relax.

03:16.106 --> 03:17.572
I know it's your birthday.

03:17.574 --> 03:19.241
Oh, thank God.

03:19.243 --> 03:21.526
Okay.

03:21.528 --> 03:22.994
I'm not telling you anything.

03:22.996 --> 03:24.663
- So there are plans.
- I didn't say that.

03:24.665 --> 03:25.664
- You said it by not saying it.
- [Groans]

03:25.666 --> 03:27.482
That is all I am saying!

03:27.484 --> 03:28.617
- Are we going someplace?
- No!

03:28.619 --> 03:30.151
Yes! We're going someplace.
Where?

03:30.153 --> 03:31.486
Stop! Udo, can you please
tell him to stop?

03:31.488 --> 03:33.255
It's not my fault.
I'm just really good at it.

03:33.257 --> 03:34.790
I thought you might
like fresh coffee.

03:34.792 --> 03:37.342
- Cool.
- Thank you.

03:37.344 --> 03:40.295
You are impossible to surprise.

03:40.297 --> 03:42.597
- You're a peeker.
- What?

03:42.599 --> 03:44.850
Somebody who tries to see
through the wrapping paper.

03:44.852 --> 03:46.501
Okay, I am in no way a peeker.

03:46.503 --> 03:47.686
- Oh, please.
- Will that be all?

03:47.688 --> 03:49.387
- Yes.
- Thank you.

03:49.389 --> 03:52.808
Now, listen up, Mr. Peeker,
because this is all

03:52.810 --> 03:54.559
you're getting.
Okay.

03:54.561 --> 03:58.480
What I have planned might
seem like a little crazy,

03:58.482 --> 04:00.031
or too much,

04:00.033 --> 04:02.033
but if you fasten
your seat belt

04:02.035 --> 04:03.568
and go with it,

04:03.570 --> 04:07.205
I promise you're gonna
have an amazing time,

04:07.207 --> 04:10.459
as long as you don't mind
interrupting your campaign.

04:10.461 --> 04:11.743
And?

04:11.745 --> 04:12.711
And if you ask
any more questions,

04:12.713 --> 04:15.330
I'm gonna call
the whole thing off.

04:15.332 --> 04:17.798
- What if I have...
- Eh.

04:17.801 --> 04:19.801
- Come on...
- Nope.

04:19.803 --> 04:22.921
- Paige...
- Eh.

04:22.923 --> 04:25.039
All right.

04:26.425 --> 04:29.094
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

04:29.096 --> 04:30.345
Wow, sounds like someone
held in

04:30.347 --> 04:31.880
their healthy breakfast today.

04:31.882 --> 04:34.649
Yes, although your trousers
aren't making it very easy.

04:34.651 --> 04:36.101
[Laughs]

04:36.103 --> 04:37.352
Hey.

04:37.354 --> 04:38.820
When I got here,
you said, "nice pants."

04:38.822 --> 04:42.724
I'm sorry I misled you.

04:42.726 --> 04:45.160
So, last night
was the official end

04:45.162 --> 04:46.561
of my first trimester,

04:46.563 --> 04:48.396
and I emailed my mother.

04:48.398 --> 04:50.565
Ah, judging by your mood,
she took the news

04:50.567 --> 04:52.033
better than you thought.
No, no.

04:52.035 --> 04:54.402
I want to tell her
I'm pregnant face-to-face.

04:54.404 --> 04:55.871
But she's been in Europe
and isn't coming back

04:55.873 --> 04:57.205
until the end of the year.

04:57.207 --> 04:59.841
Ah, Rubina's still
"finding herself"?

04:59.843 --> 05:01.259
She was...

05:01.261 --> 05:05.096
Until she found
her new boyfriend Marcello.

05:05.098 --> 05:08.416
Can you believe it?
My mother has a boyfriend.

05:08.418 --> 05:10.886
And he's insisting
that I leave today

05:10.888 --> 05:12.387
to spend a long weekend
with them

05:12.389 --> 05:14.723
at his villa in Tuscany.

05:14.725 --> 05:16.090
He sent his jet.

05:16.092 --> 05:18.560
And it seats six,
so they extended the invitation

05:18.562 --> 05:20.645
to all of hankmed.

05:20.647 --> 05:22.447
That's an amazing offer.

05:22.449 --> 05:24.649
I wish I could accept,
but I just have too much work.

05:24.651 --> 05:26.484
Jeremiah said the same thing.

05:26.486 --> 05:28.269
- You should go though.
- Really?

05:28.271 --> 05:29.321
I mean, I have work too.

05:29.323 --> 05:30.605
Nah, I got you covered.

05:30.607 --> 05:31.606
Besides, you can't wait
to talk to your mom

05:31.608 --> 05:32.908
till the end of the year.

05:32.910 --> 05:34.442
Thank you.

05:34.444 --> 05:37.128
Okay, how about you, Evan?

05:37.130 --> 05:38.129
What?

05:38.131 --> 05:39.497
Go, Ev. Go.

05:39.499 --> 05:40.882
We can give symphony
a trial run

05:40.884 --> 05:41.967
handling my schedule.

05:41.969 --> 05:44.669
- Seriously?
- Seriously.

05:44.671 --> 05:46.922
As long as you don't mind
interrupting your campaign.

05:46.924 --> 05:50.725
As long as I don't mind
interrupting my campaign.

05:50.727 --> 05:52.594
[Laughs]

05:52.596 --> 05:55.013
Okay.
Okay.

05:55.015 --> 05:58.733
Italy?
That's... that's crazy.

05:58.735 --> 05:59.851
But who am I to say no?

05:59.853 --> 06:02.437
I mean,
if it's what Paige wants.

06:02.439 --> 06:03.905
Oh, I haven't asked Paige yet.

06:03.907 --> 06:07.192
Oh, you haven't asked
Paige yet? I see.

06:07.194 --> 06:09.744
Does that mean
that I should invite her?

06:09.746 --> 06:12.914
- Well, of course you should.
- Great.

06:12.916 --> 06:16.701
So Hank and Jeremiah
can't come to Italy,

06:16.703 --> 06:19.337
and I should invite Paige.

06:19.339 --> 06:23.008
Yes. Do you have
any more questions?

06:23.010 --> 06:25.377
Questions...
no. No.

06:25.379 --> 06:26.795
No, this is me

06:26.797 --> 06:28.880
playing along,
not asking questions.

06:28.882 --> 06:31.933
No questions.
[Chuckles]

06:31.935 --> 06:34.519
And thank you.

06:34.521 --> 06:37.856
Italy.
Nice.

06:37.858 --> 06:40.675
[Laughs] Wow.

06:40.677 --> 06:42.510
Should we be worried about him?

06:42.512 --> 06:43.678
Who's "we"?

06:43.680 --> 06:45.313
You're the one
taking him to Italy.

06:45.315 --> 06:48.283
Lots of luck.

06:57.410 --> 06:59.244
Hey, there, Molly.

06:59.246 --> 07:01.046
Everything okay?

07:01.048 --> 07:02.914
Peachy.

07:02.916 --> 07:05.166
My dad's the one
you should worry about.

07:05.168 --> 07:07.869
I hear him wheezing at night.

07:07.871 --> 07:09.220
He didn't mention that to me.

07:09.222 --> 07:11.890
Oh, really, officer
I-got-this-under-control

07:11.892 --> 07:13.374
didn't complain?

07:13.376 --> 07:15.677
I know he's a little stoic.

07:15.679 --> 07:18.680
Last night,
he was hosing off the deck,

07:18.682 --> 07:19.898
and he almost fainted.

07:19.900 --> 07:22.767
And I don't have any
confidentiality rules,

07:22.769 --> 07:24.436
so I'm totally narc-ing.

07:24.438 --> 07:25.887
Which I totally appreciate.

07:25.889 --> 07:27.405
Are you sure
you don't want a ride?

07:27.407 --> 07:28.440
Uh, no.

07:28.442 --> 07:30.608
Meeting a friend.

07:30.610 --> 07:33.895
Slack?

07:33.897 --> 07:34.996
No, I'm just wondering
if your friend has a name,

07:34.998 --> 07:35.997
that's all.

07:35.999 --> 07:39.000
Her name is Mellie,

07:39.002 --> 07:40.285
so you don't have to worry

07:40.287 --> 07:42.253
'cause it's not
a boy or anything.

07:42.255 --> 07:45.073
Okay.

07:45.075 --> 07:46.541
See you later, doctor.

07:46.543 --> 07:49.544
See you later, Molly.

07:49.546 --> 07:51.930
[Engine revs]

08:00.106 --> 08:03.108
[Upbeat music]

08:03.121 --> 08:04.742
<font color="#40bfff">Sync & corrections by <font color="#FFA500">wilson0804</font></font>
