08:09.094 --> 08:10.712
This weekend?

08:10.714 --> 08:13.381
Gee, Evan, I'm pretty busy
with Russel.

08:13.383 --> 08:14.465
[Chuckles]

08:14.467 --> 08:15.683
Well, I have a feeling

08:15.685 --> 08:17.051
it will all work out somehow.

08:17.053 --> 08:18.636
I mean we're talking Italy here,
right?

08:18.638 --> 08:19.854
We're talking Tuscany.

08:19.856 --> 08:21.105
It's like my dream trip.

08:21.107 --> 08:22.640
Our dream trip,

08:22.642 --> 08:24.692
which we are now taking
with Divya?

08:24.694 --> 08:26.694
Yeah, genius touch by the way.

08:26.696 --> 08:27.695
Huh?

08:27.697 --> 08:29.063
Oh, nothing.
Nothing at all.

08:29.065 --> 08:31.232
So I was just calling to see,

08:31.234 --> 08:32.734
should I pack my linen suit

08:32.736 --> 08:34.152
or do I need something
a little more formal?

08:34.154 --> 08:36.270
I don't know.
Why don't you ask Divya?

08:36.272 --> 08:37.956
You really want to do this?

08:37.957 --> 08:39.490
Of course I do.
Are you kidding?

08:39.491 --> 08:41.876
Uh, maybe Russel can drop me
off at the airport

08:41.878 --> 08:44.629
when we're done here
in the city.

08:44.631 --> 08:47.465
Can you pack me a bag?

08:47.467 --> 08:49.784
Wait, you want me to pack
for you?

08:49.786 --> 08:51.753
Listen, Evan, I really got
to get back to work.

08:51.755 --> 08:53.721
I will call you when
I get to the airport, okay?

08:53.723 --> 08:54.923
All right.
See you there.

08:54.925 --> 08:56.975
Sorry.

08:56.977 --> 08:59.727
And I thought I was
the neediest man in your life.

08:59.729 --> 09:04.482
♪ <i>'O sole mio</i> ♪

09:04.484 --> 09:08.135
♪ <i>'o sole mio</i> ♪

09:08.137 --> 09:11.689
♪ and Happy Birthday

09:11.691 --> 09:15.309
♪ to

09:15.311 --> 09:23.250
♪ me

09:23.370 --> 09:25.203
[boat horn blows]

09:25.205 --> 09:27.005
You said I'd experience
some light-headedness

09:27.007 --> 09:28.589
when I came off the prednisone.

09:28.591 --> 09:30.758
Yeah, I also said to keep me
in the loop.

09:30.760 --> 09:32.427
How often have you felt faint?

09:32.429 --> 09:33.828
[Chuckles]

09:33.830 --> 09:36.014
What sounds lamer...
"light-headed" or "faint"?

09:36.016 --> 09:38.466
Would you prefer "woozy"?

09:38.468 --> 09:39.600
Look, it's only happened
a couple times.

09:39.602 --> 09:41.052
And I've never lost
consciousness.

09:41.054 --> 09:42.353
Mmhmm.

09:42.355 --> 09:44.472
Well, your EKG isn't alarming,

09:44.474 --> 09:48.309
but I am seeing a couple
of nonconducted p-waves.

09:48.311 --> 09:49.527
Abnormal rhythm.

09:49.529 --> 09:50.895
It's probably a non-finding,

09:50.897 --> 09:52.230
but I'd still like
to schedule an mri.

09:52.232 --> 09:54.399
Why are you worried
about my heart?

09:54.401 --> 09:57.518
With your sarcoidosis,
we need to be extra careful.

09:57.520 --> 10:01.239
If your girlish swoons
are due to an arrhythmia,

10:01.241 --> 10:02.874
you can develop heart block.

10:02.876 --> 10:04.042
Heart block.

10:04.044 --> 10:05.860
That sounds manly.
I could live with that.

10:05.862 --> 10:07.996
Actually, you can't.

10:07.998 --> 10:10.999
It could mean sudden death.

10:13.502 --> 10:15.586
The Van Der Gelts are
very special clients,

10:15.588 --> 10:17.588
but I think we can trust
the delivery men

10:17.590 --> 10:19.540
to bring the piece in safely.

10:19.542 --> 10:20.641
Along with all the other items?

10:20.643 --> 10:22.727
Other items?

10:22.729 --> 10:24.846
Apparently,
our very special client

10:24.848 --> 10:26.881
went on
an Asian shopping spree.

10:26.883 --> 10:29.600
There's a truck full, including

10:29.602 --> 10:31.552
siamese temple figures,

10:31.554 --> 10:34.388
a 600-pound
Tibetan monastery bell,

10:34.390 --> 10:35.990
a 19th century...
Please stop.

10:35.992 --> 10:37.992
Certainly the Van Der Gelts
cannot expect...

10:37.994 --> 10:42.080
the Van Der Gelts can expect.
And we can do.

10:50.456 --> 10:52.006
- <i>Grazie.</i>
<i>- Si.</i>

10:52.008 --> 10:53.374
Ugh.
What's that?

10:53.376 --> 10:54.742
Hold on.
Hold on.

10:54.744 --> 10:55.793
I'm turning you up.

10:55.795 --> 10:57.428
[Grunts]

10:57.430 --> 10:59.547
Okay, say that again.

10:59.549 --> 11:01.916
What?

11:01.918 --> 11:03.301
Oh, my God.
That's so horrible.

11:03.303 --> 11:04.752
Paige says she can't make it.

11:04.754 --> 11:06.587
She has to "work all night."

11:06.589 --> 11:08.022
Oh, that's such a shame.

11:08.024 --> 11:09.440
Oh, that's right.

11:09.442 --> 11:12.477
Yeah, there's a flight
to Florence

11:12.479 --> 11:14.695
I could try to catch
in the morning,

11:14.697 --> 11:16.781
if you guys want to go ahead
without me.

11:16.783 --> 11:19.784
Evan, my ob says I'm fine
to travel alone.

11:19.786 --> 11:21.435
You should not feel obligated.

11:21.437 --> 11:24.572
So you want me to go
without you...

11:24.574 --> 11:28.126
Paige?

11:28.128 --> 11:29.494
I give up.

11:29.496 --> 11:31.412
I have no idea where you are.

11:31.414 --> 11:34.165
No idea where you are.

11:34.167 --> 11:36.167
Paige!

11:36.169 --> 11:38.302
I'm here.
Evan, can you hear me?

11:38.304 --> 11:40.838
Yeah. You're here where?

11:40.840 --> 11:42.123
At the Van Der Gelts.

11:42.125 --> 11:43.624
Haven't you been listening?

11:43.626 --> 11:47.311
[Speaking italian]

11:47.313 --> 11:48.629
<i>Si, si.</i>

11:48.631 --> 11:51.315
[Speaking italian]

11:51.317 --> 11:52.316
<i>Prego.</i>

11:52.318 --> 11:53.467
Evan.

11:53.469 --> 11:55.186
I think he might be asking you

11:55.188 --> 11:57.105
to take your seat,
fasten your seat belt,

11:57.107 --> 11:59.357
so we can take off.

11:59.359 --> 12:03.244
Right.
Fasten my seat belt.

12:03.246 --> 12:06.280
Very good.
Very good.

12:06.282 --> 12:07.648
[Laughs]

12:07.650 --> 12:09.984
Okay, I'm going with it.
Going with it.

12:09.986 --> 12:11.953
Not asking questions.
Seat belt fastened.

12:11.955 --> 12:13.421
Are you sure
that you shouldn't stay?

12:13.423 --> 12:14.672
No, Paige wants me
to play along.

12:14.674 --> 12:15.823
Um, <i>ciao, Bella.</i>

12:15.825 --> 12:17.708
I'll see you there.
I love you.

12:17.710 --> 12:20.962
Evan? Evan?

12:20.964 --> 12:22.463
[Sighs]

12:22.465 --> 12:25.800
What are you looking at?

12:29.671 --> 12:31.439
If you see her,
tell her to call me

12:31.441 --> 12:32.974
or her dad.

12:32.976 --> 12:36.343
Okay, so what's your excuse
this time?

12:36.345 --> 12:38.229
Molly said she was spending
the night with a friend.

12:38.231 --> 12:39.697
This morning I found out
it's not true.

12:39.699 --> 12:40.848
Nobody knows where she is.

12:40.850 --> 12:42.366
Oh, I'm sorry.

12:42.368 --> 12:43.401
What about the kids
in the park?

12:43.403 --> 12:45.069
I'm texting them now.

12:45.071 --> 12:47.738
She isn't with Mellie?

12:47.740 --> 12:48.789
Mellie?

12:48.791 --> 12:50.191
Yeah, when I saw her yesterday,

12:50.193 --> 12:53.461
she said she was meeting
her friend, Mellie.

12:53.463 --> 12:55.046
Okay, okay.

12:55.048 --> 12:57.531
Now I know where she is.

12:57.533 --> 13:00.051
I used to have an old house
on the North Fork

13:00.053 --> 13:01.702
that I had to sell years ago.

13:01.704 --> 13:04.338
The folks who bought it
let it go to ruin.

13:04.340 --> 13:06.140
We heard this week that
it was gonna be demolished.

13:06.142 --> 13:07.975
And that made Molly mad.
I mean, what doesn't?

13:07.977 --> 13:10.394
So Mellie lives
in your old neighborhood?

13:10.396 --> 13:12.730
No, that was Molly
blowing you off.

13:12.732 --> 13:15.816
Mellie was her imaginary friend
from when she was a child.

13:15.818 --> 13:17.185
After her mom left,

13:17.187 --> 13:18.736
Mellie was her way of coping.

13:18.738 --> 13:20.054
Ah. Okay.

13:20.056 --> 13:21.272
But why isn't
she answering her phone?

13:21.274 --> 13:22.573
Well, there's no service
out there.

13:22.575 --> 13:24.058
Where did you see her yesterday?

13:24.060 --> 13:26.244
By the bus stop near 27.

13:26.246 --> 13:29.113
No, there's no bus that goes
out to our old place.

13:29.115 --> 13:31.415
She was just west of town
out by the warehouse.

13:32.901 --> 13:34.452
Well, that's a place
where kids hitch rides.

13:34.454 --> 13:36.787
Okay, come on.
I'll drive you out there now.

13:36.789 --> 13:39.307
- Call me if she shows up.
- Yes, sir.

13:40.697 --> 13:42.698
[Italian folk music]

13:46.236 --> 13:47.786
Okay, so this is Firenze

13:47.788 --> 13:51.206
and this is Gaiole in Chianti,

13:51.208 --> 13:52.607
then we're lost.
[Sighs]

13:52.609 --> 13:54.943
If you were a better navigator,
we wouldn't be lost.

13:54.945 --> 13:56.795
Yeah, or if you had
accepted Marcello's offer

13:56.797 --> 13:58.547
to send us a town car, Divya.

13:58.549 --> 13:59.548
We're in Italy.

13:59.550 --> 14:01.550
I love driving here.

14:01.552 --> 14:03.135
Oh, really?
You love driving here?

14:03.137 --> 14:05.004
Where is "here"?

14:05.006 --> 14:08.140
<i>Scusa, marito di sheeps,</i>

14:08.142 --> 14:10.592
<i>spariti noi stessi...</i>

14:10.594 --> 14:11.760
[sheep bleat]

14:11.762 --> 14:13.729
I don't think he can hear me.

14:13.731 --> 14:14.980
Yeah, I think he did.

14:14.982 --> 14:16.148
Oh, my God.

14:16.150 --> 14:17.933
Should we be worried
about Toscana virus?

14:17.935 --> 14:19.685
Toscana virus is transmitted

14:19.687 --> 14:23.322
by the bite of a sand flea,
not by passing sheep.

14:23.324 --> 14:25.240
It's called Toscana virus,
Divya, okay?

14:25.242 --> 14:26.275
We're in Tuscany.

14:26.277 --> 14:27.576
You don't know where we are.

14:27.578 --> 14:28.911
I'm not supposed to know.

14:28.913 --> 14:30.446
I'm supposed to be surprised.

14:30.448 --> 14:32.031
[Groans] Ugh...

14:32.033 --> 14:33.665
Oh, signor.

14:33.667 --> 14:34.750
<i>Scusi, signore.</i>

14:34.752 --> 14:37.336
<i>Scusa.</i>

14:37.338 --> 14:38.420
[Speaking italian]

14:38.422 --> 14:40.655
<i>Si.</i>
<i>Yes, we are lost.</i>

14:40.657 --> 14:41.656
- Yes.
- Ah.

14:41.658 --> 14:43.158
Honeymooners?

14:43.160 --> 14:45.260
Us?
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

14:45.262 --> 14:46.328
- [Laughs] No.
- We are not together.

14:46.330 --> 14:47.629
<i>Bella.</i>

14:47.631 --> 14:49.181
Um, my name is gino.

14:49.183 --> 14:51.500
Come, there is a big party
at my Uncle's villa,

14:51.502 --> 14:53.052
and I need a date.

14:53.054 --> 14:54.603
Okay, sorry, gino,

14:54.605 --> 14:58.190
but we have our own party
to get to in oregano.

14:58.192 --> 14:59.441
- Origo.
- Origo?

14:59.443 --> 15:01.860
Origo... that's
where <i>Mio Zio</i> lives.

15:01.862 --> 15:03.612
Are you going to villa Fucci?

15:03.614 --> 15:05.230
Yes, yes, yes.
Marcello Fucci's house.

15:05.232 --> 15:08.117
<i>Perfetto.</i>
<i>You follow me.</i>

15:08.119 --> 15:09.151
Oh, my God.

15:09.153 --> 15:10.119
Hey.

15:10.121 --> 15:13.739
[Speaking italian]

15:14.857 --> 15:16.875
Eh...[Mutters].

15:18.211 --> 15:19.878
- Okay.
- <i>Molto freddo?</i>

15:19.880 --> 15:22.247
Yeah. It means very cool.
Unless it's <i>Molto Frodo.</i>

15:22.249 --> 15:23.715
No, no, no.
Frodo's a hobbit.

15:23.717 --> 15:25.717
Please let this be
a short trip.

15:31.674 --> 15:32.707
[Engine shuts off]

15:42.652 --> 15:43.735
Here.

15:43.737 --> 15:44.853
[Grunts]

15:44.855 --> 15:46.388
Here, come through there.

15:46.390 --> 15:48.723
Molly!
Molly, are you here?

15:48.725 --> 15:51.726
Dad!
Dad, I'm up here.

15:53.113 --> 15:54.913
Daddy!

15:54.915 --> 15:55.998
Molly!
Molly!

15:56.000 --> 15:57.833
It hurts bad,
it hurts real bad.

15:57.835 --> 15:59.418
Sorry, baby.
I'm here. I'm here.

15:59.420 --> 16:00.536
Everything's gonna be okay.

16:00.538 --> 16:01.736
Everything...
Okay, careful.

16:01.738 --> 16:03.755
This floor may not hold.

16:05.091 --> 16:08.627
[Molly whimpers]

16:08.629 --> 16:11.413
Molly, how long
have you been trapped here?

16:11.415 --> 16:13.382
I, um, a few hours.

16:13.384 --> 16:15.467
- I'm... l'm sorry.
- It's okay, baby.

16:15.469 --> 16:16.718
Your pulse is strong.
That's good.

16:16.720 --> 16:18.520
But I can't rule out blood loss

16:18.522 --> 16:19.921
until I get a look at your leg.

16:19.923 --> 16:21.440
Maybe I should try
and pry the wood.

16:21.442 --> 16:23.859
You know what, first toss me
those old packing blankets.

16:23.861 --> 16:26.478
She's showing early signs
of hypothermia.

16:26.480 --> 16:28.430
If you can get a cell signal,
call 911, okay?

16:31.201 --> 16:34.036
I-I just wanted
to spend one more night,

16:34.038 --> 16:35.621
- then... then the floor broke.
- Damn!

16:35.623 --> 16:36.905
It's okay, it's okay,
it's okay.

16:36.907 --> 16:38.207
We're gonna get you
out of here.

16:38.209 --> 16:40.209
All right.

16:40.211 --> 16:42.211
Let me get in here.

16:45.448 --> 16:47.282
[Yelps] Ow!

16:47.284 --> 16:48.584
[Tool thuds] Ow!

16:48.586 --> 16:49.801
You need to take it easy,
all right?

16:49.803 --> 16:51.803
The boards aren't going
to break.

16:53.223 --> 16:56.341
[Crying]

16:56.343 --> 16:58.060
Hey, don.

16:58.062 --> 16:59.461
Maybe if you push against
these boards

16:59.463 --> 17:01.230
towards me, okay?

17:01.232 --> 17:03.131
I'll use this blanket...
To cushion her leg.

17:03.133 --> 17:06.484
Yeah, exactly.

17:06.487 --> 17:07.801
All right, just lean into it.

17:07.804 --> 17:10.105
Not too much.
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

17:10.107 --> 17:11.740
All right, stop, stop, stop.

17:11.742 --> 17:13.358
Can you give her something
for the pain?

17:13.359 --> 17:16.862
I have morphine,
but that's pretty strong stuff.

17:16.864 --> 17:18.780
Okay.

17:18.781 --> 17:20.982
Molly, take one
of these hydrocodone.

17:20.983 --> 17:22.166
- Okay.
- It'll help.

17:22.169 --> 17:23.417
That's your prescription.

17:23.420 --> 17:25.871
Good thing you didn't kick
the habit, huh?

17:25.873 --> 17:27.372
Yeah.

17:27.374 --> 17:30.092
All right.
Can you swallow that, Molly?

17:30.094 --> 17:32.094
- Yeah.
- Good. Here.

17:34.547 --> 17:36.348
Okay, we'll give the medication

17:36.350 --> 17:38.517
a little while to kick in.

17:38.519 --> 17:41.520
[Italian folk music]

17:41.522 --> 17:42.022
♪

17:48.062 --> 17:50.979
This is really elaborate.

17:52.515 --> 17:55.234
Oh, your mom,
she's actually here.

17:55.236 --> 17:57.569
Why shouldn't she be?

17:57.571 --> 18:01.189
'Cause it's my birthday.

18:03.526 --> 18:05.244
[Tapping glass]

18:05.246 --> 18:06.962
<i>Attenzione, per favore.</i>

18:06.964 --> 18:09.531
So welcome, everybody.

18:09.533 --> 18:11.533
Welcome, friends and family,

18:11.535 --> 18:14.703
and especially our guests
from New York,

18:14.705 --> 18:17.556
Rubina's lovely daughter,
Divya,

18:17.558 --> 18:19.675
who we're so happy
to have her with us

18:19.677 --> 18:21.927
for this very special toast.

18:21.929 --> 18:23.729
<i>Aspetta, Marcello!</i>

18:23.731 --> 18:26.565
Wait!

18:26.567 --> 18:29.067
A special toast
needs a special wine.

18:29.069 --> 18:32.053
My brother Massimo.
He always spoils everything.

18:32.055 --> 18:33.071
[Whispers] Divya.

18:33.073 --> 18:35.274
Divya. Divs.
Hmm?

18:35.276 --> 18:37.159
What's going on?
What's the holdup?

18:37.161 --> 18:40.078
Apparently we need special
wine for a special toast.

18:40.080 --> 18:42.247
Ah,<i>perfetto.</i>

18:42.249 --> 18:43.949
Very good.

18:43.951 --> 18:46.118
Better get rid of this, right?

18:51.240 --> 18:52.240
Gah!

18:54.910 --> 18:55.910
Okay, you ready?

18:55.912 --> 18:57.596
All right. On three.
Yeah.

18:57.598 --> 18:59.715
One, two,

18:59.717 --> 19:00.716
three!

19:00.718 --> 19:02.934
[Both grunt]

19:02.936 --> 19:03.935
Got it, got it.

19:03.937 --> 19:05.470
Okay.
Easy, easy.

19:05.472 --> 19:07.255
Ah, good.
And she's out.

19:07.257 --> 19:09.858
[Pants]

19:09.860 --> 19:11.143
Y... You're okay, Molly?

19:11.145 --> 19:12.227
- Yeah.
- All right, baby.

19:12.229 --> 19:14.229
- Yeah.
- [Kisses]

19:16.316 --> 19:18.533
Don, can you apply pressure
to the wound right here?

19:18.535 --> 19:20.035
- Yeah.
- Just press.

19:20.037 --> 19:21.953
Okay.

19:21.955 --> 19:25.157
It's okay, baby.
It's okay.

19:25.159 --> 19:27.492
I can still feel
a pulse in her leg.

19:27.494 --> 19:28.543
It's a good sign.

19:28.545 --> 19:29.828
- Thank you.
- It's good.

19:29.830 --> 19:30.945
It's good.

19:30.947 --> 19:32.998
Okay, Molly, can you feel this?

19:33.000 --> 19:34.333
Yeah.

19:34.335 --> 19:35.634
Okay, good.
Can you wiggle your toes?

19:35.636 --> 19:37.803
- Um, mm-hmm.
- Okay. Good.

19:37.805 --> 19:40.472
Gosh, she's still losing blood.

19:40.474 --> 19:43.124
Riverhead's
the closest hospital.

19:43.126 --> 19:46.094
Okay, I just need to wrap it
with a pressure dressing,

19:46.096 --> 19:47.479
and then we can go.

19:47.481 --> 19:49.631
There we go.

19:49.633 --> 19:51.800
You're gonna be okay, Molly.

19:51.802 --> 19:53.685
Okay, we should be able
to get a cell signal

19:53.687 --> 19:55.270
within a few Miles.
Yeah.

19:55.272 --> 19:56.521
All right.
Let's get moving.

19:56.523 --> 19:57.939
I got it, I got it.

19:57.941 --> 19:59.474
- Come on, baby. Ready?
- Mmhmm.

19:59.476 --> 20:01.243
Let's go.
One, two, three.

20:01.245 --> 20:04.196
All right, here we go.

20:04.198 --> 20:07.416
Now, while this is not really

20:07.418 --> 20:12.037
an official engagement party,

20:12.039 --> 20:14.539
you see, Rubina
would like our divorces

20:14.541 --> 20:16.375
to be finalized first.

20:16.377 --> 20:20.011
I believe this to be
an ancient hindu custom.

20:20.013 --> 20:21.263
[Laughter]

20:21.265 --> 20:23.382
But given Marcello's
catholic faith,

20:23.384 --> 20:25.517
divorce may never happen,

20:25.519 --> 20:27.269
so we may have to live in sin.

20:27.271 --> 20:28.470
Oh, that's not bad.

20:28.472 --> 20:30.355
[Glasses clink]
[Laughs] Cheers.

20:30.357 --> 20:32.691
Divya, I thought
you would like my surprise.

20:32.693 --> 20:34.810
Do you disapprove?

20:34.812 --> 20:36.528
Of course not.

20:36.530 --> 20:38.897
It's just that
your surprise is...

20:38.899 --> 20:40.449
It's so surprising.

20:40.451 --> 20:43.952
I'm happy that you're happy.

20:43.954 --> 20:46.905
Yes, but you did not
drink to us.

20:46.907 --> 20:49.124
Oh, oh, oh.
No, no.

20:49.126 --> 20:51.710
It's... it's not that.

20:52.712 --> 20:54.713
I can't drink.

20:54.715 --> 20:56.748
- Ah.
- I don't understand.

21:01.754 --> 21:06.224
Mummy, I have a surprise
of my own.

21:08.394 --> 21:10.211
I'm pregnant.

21:10.213 --> 21:11.763
[Chuckles]

21:11.765 --> 21:13.047
<i>Incinta.</i>

21:13.049 --> 21:14.215
[Murmuring]

21:14.217 --> 21:15.734
Cheers.

21:15.736 --> 21:18.069
But I thought...

21:19.605 --> 21:23.408
well, that is a surprise.

21:23.410 --> 21:25.744
Yes. It is.

21:25.746 --> 21:28.997
I'm sure you'll both be
wonderful parents.

21:28.999 --> 21:30.415
No, no, no, no.

21:30.417 --> 21:31.950
No, no, no.
I'm not the father.

21:31.952 --> 21:35.420
Mama, I had a fling.

21:35.422 --> 21:38.673
With a famous polo player
and underwear model.

21:38.675 --> 21:40.759
Same guy.

21:40.761 --> 21:42.210
I'm a little confused.

21:42.212 --> 21:43.628
That makes two of us.

21:43.630 --> 21:45.213
Can we talk for one second,
Divya. Just one second.

21:45.215 --> 21:48.216
One second.

21:50.102 --> 21:51.920
Why do I have a feeling

21:51.922 --> 21:53.188
you're about to make this
all about you?

21:53.190 --> 21:55.590
This isn't my birthday party,
is it?

21:55.592 --> 21:58.026
It's your birthday?

21:58.028 --> 21:59.528
Mmhmm.

21:59.530 --> 22:03.064
Oh, my gosh, I am so sorry.

22:03.066 --> 22:04.699
Happy Birthday.

22:04.701 --> 22:06.485
Oh, thank you, thank you.

22:06.487 --> 22:09.704
But Evan, shouldn't you
be spending it with Paige?

22:09.706 --> 22:11.940
That's what I thought
I was doing, Divya.

22:11.942 --> 22:13.124
I thought this whole thing
was a plan

22:13.126 --> 22:14.543
she cooked up to surprise me.

22:14.545 --> 22:17.996
What? Why on earth
would you think that?

22:17.998 --> 22:20.114
'Cause it seemed awesome.

22:20.116 --> 22:22.300
No wonder you've been acting
especially insane.

22:22.302 --> 22:24.169
I have to get out of here.

22:24.171 --> 22:27.055
I have to get home.
I have to call Paige.

22:27.057 --> 22:28.924
No bars. Great.

22:28.926 --> 22:30.225
Come on.

22:30.227 --> 22:31.893
Bars.

22:31.895 --> 22:33.228
Give me bars.

22:33.230 --> 22:36.130
Give me bars.
Give me bars.

22:36.132 --> 22:37.232
Bars.

22:37.234 --> 22:39.267
I have no...

22:39.269 --> 22:40.268
I have bars.

22:40.270 --> 22:43.738
[Laughs] I have bars.

22:43.740 --> 22:45.740
Hi, this is Paige.
Please leave a message.

22:45.742 --> 22:47.192
Babe, I'm so sorry.

22:47.194 --> 22:49.194
I accidentally came
to Italy without you.

22:49.196 --> 22:50.579
I thought the whole thing...
[Beep beep]

22:50.581 --> 22:52.981
Was your pla...
hello? No.

22:52.983 --> 22:55.534
No bars. No bars.

22:55.536 --> 22:58.537
Just give me one bar.
Give me some cars.

22:58.539 --> 23:00.488
Please give me bars!

23:02.430 --> 23:03.847
Any service yet?

23:03.849 --> 23:05.732
We should get a signal
in about a mile.

23:05.734 --> 23:06.733
Okay.

23:06.735 --> 23:09.603
They just let it rot.

23:09.605 --> 23:12.022
Our house.

23:12.024 --> 23:13.574
Should she be so loopy?

23:13.576 --> 23:16.309
Well, the hydrocodone's
controlling her pain,

23:16.311 --> 23:18.829
but it will make her drowsy
and weak for a few hours.

23:18.831 --> 23:20.581
She might also have
some confusion

23:20.583 --> 23:22.282
and emotional lability.

23:22.284 --> 23:23.333
Lability?

23:23.335 --> 23:25.085
Mood swings.

23:25.087 --> 23:28.589
They bought it
only to demolish it.

23:28.591 --> 23:32.259
[Thumps]
They're horrible people!

23:32.261 --> 23:34.678
I hate them!

23:34.680 --> 23:36.430
Got it.

23:36.432 --> 23:39.349
[Cries] We should stop
the bulldozers.

23:39.351 --> 23:41.334
Please at least try.

23:41.336 --> 23:43.353
Honey, listen.
We both loved that house.

23:43.355 --> 23:44.555
We're just gonna have to
remember that...

23:44.557 --> 23:46.506
no, no.
We have to save it.

23:46.508 --> 23:47.891
Turn around.
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Molly!

23:47.893 --> 23:50.894
- Molly!
Both: Molly!

23:50.896 --> 23:52.512
[Tires screech]

23:53.615 --> 23:54.615
Whoa!

23:54.617 --> 23:55.649
[Both groaning]

23:55.651 --> 23:57.117
Oh.

23:57.119 --> 23:59.403
Is everyone okay?
Molly, sweetheart, you okay?

23:59.405 --> 24:02.539
Yeah. I-I didn't mean to...

24:02.541 --> 24:04.524
I'm... I'm sorry.
Any pain?

24:04.526 --> 24:06.243
- No, I'm sorry.
- It's okay, it's okay.

24:06.245 --> 24:07.628
Stay where you are.

24:07.630 --> 24:09.463
It's better to keep
your leg elevated.

24:12.383 --> 24:14.200
We'll need something
for traction.

24:14.202 --> 24:16.202
- Yeah.
- I'll go take a look.

24:20.592 --> 24:22.309
Ow.

24:22.311 --> 24:23.760
Ooh.

24:23.762 --> 24:25.012
Molly!

24:25.014 --> 24:26.880
No, it's... it's fine.
I'm okay.

24:26.882 --> 24:28.214
Can't you listen to Hank?

24:28.216 --> 24:31.235
It's fine.
It's gonna be elevated, okay?

24:31.237 --> 24:32.886
We're not sunk that deep.

24:32.888 --> 24:35.055
- I can push us out.
- No, I'll push. You steer.

24:35.057 --> 24:37.491
You've exerted yourself
too much already.

24:37.493 --> 24:40.777
There we go.

24:40.779 --> 24:42.112
Okay.

24:42.114 --> 24:44.248
All right, good.

24:50.288 --> 24:52.072
Okay, turn it over.
All right.

24:52.074 --> 24:54.074
[Engine turns over]

24:57.745 --> 24:59.963
[Grunts]

24:59.965 --> 25:01.965
Okay, easy, easy.

25:01.967 --> 25:03.800
All right.

25:03.802 --> 25:05.469
I put it into neutral.

25:05.471 --> 25:07.187
Let's do this together on three.
No, no, no.

25:07.189 --> 25:08.472
Don, you shouldn't be...
Come on.

25:08.474 --> 25:11.024
One, two, three.
All right.

25:11.026 --> 25:13.193
[Both grunt]

25:13.195 --> 25:14.311
Don?

25:14.313 --> 25:16.313
Don?

25:23.437 --> 25:25.656
Don? Don?

25:25.658 --> 25:27.324
What happened?

25:27.326 --> 25:29.576
Molly, I need you to try 911.

25:29.578 --> 25:30.777
911?

25:30.779 --> 25:33.714
What is it about "no service"

25:33.716 --> 25:36.466
that you guys don't understand.

25:36.468 --> 25:38.635
Dad?

25:38.637 --> 25:40.120
What's... what's going on?
What are you doing?

25:40.122 --> 25:41.972
What are you doi...
dad? Dad?

25:41.974 --> 25:43.957
Molly, just try to call now.

25:43.959 --> 25:45.976
He'll be okay,
but he needs our help, okay?

25:45.978 --> 25:47.477
Oh, God.

25:47.479 --> 25:50.230
No, no, no.
No, no. No, no.

25:50.232 --> 25:52.316
Uh, oh, no.

25:52.318 --> 25:53.900
Ah!
Oh, it's ringing.

25:53.902 --> 25:55.301
Hi, okay. Hi.

25:55.303 --> 25:58.772
Yes, there's a police officer
hurt on middle path

25:58.774 --> 26:00.691
east of Mattituck...

26:00.693 --> 26:01.908
tell them he needs
immediate assistance.

26:01.910 --> 26:04.161
It... it dropped.

26:04.163 --> 26:05.162
Well, did they hear you?

26:05.164 --> 26:06.613
I don't know!

26:06.615 --> 26:08.982
God, what's happening?

26:08.984 --> 26:11.001
Molly!
Molly, look at me right now.

26:11.003 --> 26:12.586
I need you to go in the trunk,

26:12.588 --> 26:14.087
and get my bag, okay?
Okay.

26:14.089 --> 26:15.756
Your dad just needs
some help breathing.

26:15.758 --> 26:18.091
When did he stop breathing?
Oh, my God.

26:18.093 --> 26:19.343
Oh, my God.

26:21.012 --> 26:23.180
What's... what is that for?

26:23.182 --> 26:25.716
I'm trying to start his heart.
Don't touch him.

26:25.718 --> 26:27.300
Oh, my God.
His heart stopped?

26:27.302 --> 26:29.269
What did... what did you do
to him?

26:29.271 --> 26:31.838
Okay, stand clear.

26:31.840 --> 26:33.974
[Electric zap]

26:33.976 --> 26:35.058
Ugh.

26:35.060 --> 26:36.059
No? Didn't...

26:36.061 --> 26:37.611
didn't work? No?

26:37.613 --> 26:39.279
Do... do it again!

26:39.281 --> 26:41.898
Not yet, I need to get
his circulation up first.

26:44.152 --> 26:47.854
Okay, let's just try
another shock, okay?

26:47.856 --> 26:49.373
Stand clear again, please.

26:49.375 --> 26:51.041
Stay with me, Molly.
Okay.

26:51.043 --> 26:53.693
Stay with me, okay.

26:53.695 --> 26:55.912
[Electric zap]

26:55.914 --> 26:58.131
Ah!
No, no.

26:58.133 --> 27:00.200
No, no. No, no, no.
Dad!

27:00.202 --> 27:02.636
No, don't die.
Come on. Come on.

27:02.638 --> 27:04.254
You can't die.

27:04.256 --> 27:06.423
This isn't working.
This isn't working.

27:06.425 --> 27:07.424
I have to intubate.

27:07.426 --> 27:08.541
Okay.

27:08.543 --> 27:11.211
Do it!
What are you waiting for?

27:11.213 --> 27:13.597
Well, the procedure's better
done in a hospital, but...

27:13.599 --> 27:15.215
All right,
I'm gonna try an LMA.

27:15.217 --> 27:16.566
That should give us
a more secure airway.

27:16.568 --> 27:19.219
Okay.

27:19.221 --> 27:20.887
Hurry!

27:20.889 --> 27:22.105
Hurry up!
Come on!

27:22.107 --> 27:23.389
Don't let him die.

27:23.391 --> 27:25.225
You said that you wouldn't
let him die!

27:25.227 --> 27:26.827
Molly, shh.
Just calm down, okay?

27:26.829 --> 27:28.578
I need to get this
into his throat.

27:28.580 --> 27:33.900
Now can you hold his head still
for me?

27:33.902 --> 27:36.420
Good.

27:36.422 --> 27:38.872
Okay.

27:38.874 --> 27:42.125
And here we go, don.

27:42.127 --> 27:44.077
[Don gagging]

27:44.079 --> 27:45.846
What's wrong?

27:45.848 --> 27:49.582
He may have aspirated a bit,
but... I'm in.

27:49.584 --> 27:52.085
- Okay.
- Okay. I need this.

27:52.087 --> 27:53.220
Oh, sorry.

27:57.642 --> 27:59.926
Is he getting air?

27:59.928 --> 28:02.595
He is now.

28:02.597 --> 28:05.699
I want to try one more time.

28:05.701 --> 28:07.784
Okay, stand clear.

28:07.786 --> 28:09.286
Come on, don.

28:09.288 --> 28:11.872
God.

28:11.874 --> 28:13.457
Okay.

28:13.459 --> 28:15.608
Sinus rhythm.

28:15.610 --> 28:17.160
[Cries]

28:17.162 --> 28:18.945
Yep, I'm getting a pulse.
His heart is working.

28:18.947 --> 28:21.915
[Crying] Oh, my God.

28:23.885 --> 28:25.252
Is he gonna wake up?

28:25.254 --> 28:27.120
He's out of V-fib,
he's getting oxygen.

28:27.122 --> 28:28.305
[Sirens wail]

28:28.307 --> 28:32.893
And it sounds
like your call went through.

28:35.906 --> 28:38.465
Divya, this was a mistake.
I'm gonna miss my flight.

28:38.467 --> 28:40.200
No, we're taking a shortcut.

28:40.202 --> 28:42.969
This is not a...
this is a dirt road!

28:42.971 --> 28:43.987
Stop the car.
Stop.

28:43.989 --> 28:45.238
Pull over right now.

28:45.240 --> 28:47.240
Just pull over.

28:49.977 --> 28:52.328
Are you going to be sick again?

28:52.330 --> 28:54.497
No, I'm okay.

28:54.499 --> 28:57.617
No, I'm not.

29:00.704 --> 29:03.757
[Vomits]

29:11.999 --> 29:13.633
All better?

29:13.635 --> 29:16.936
Uhh...

29:16.938 --> 29:19.606
I think I have
the Toscana virus.

29:19.608 --> 29:21.340
Or I guess some kind of parasite

29:21.342 --> 29:23.176
from that raw pork carpaccio?

29:23.178 --> 29:25.895
It wasn't raw pork.
It was raw beef.

29:25.897 --> 29:27.513
Sorry.

29:27.515 --> 29:28.898
Wait

29:30.234 --> 29:31.618
[groans] Uhh...

29:31.620 --> 29:34.187
You are suffering
from too much stress

29:34.189 --> 29:35.538
and too much chianti.

29:35.540 --> 29:37.240
Don't... don't say that word,
please.

29:37.242 --> 29:39.709
Even the thought of wine...

29:39.711 --> 29:42.712
[exhales]

29:45.032 --> 29:46.332
Why won't she call back?

29:46.334 --> 29:48.918
Do you have a signal?

29:48.920 --> 29:51.805
I have one bar...
I have no bars.

29:51.807 --> 29:54.307
It's very weak.
We should keep driving.

29:54.309 --> 29:56.375
Come on.
[Phone chimes]

29:56.377 --> 29:57.594
It's her.
Oh, my God.

29:57.596 --> 29:58.895
Paige!

29:58.897 --> 30:00.980
Evan? What's wrong?

30:00.982 --> 30:03.566
[Groans]
Oh. It's a nightmare.

30:03.568 --> 30:05.218
I'm... I'm dying here.

30:05.220 --> 30:07.320
- Are you sick?
- Yes, I'm miserable.

30:07.322 --> 30:09.072
I drank too much.

30:09.074 --> 30:10.323
Poor you.

30:10.325 --> 30:12.892
No, Divya's taking care of me,
so...

30:12.894 --> 30:15.945
you called six times to tell
me you're drunk with Divya?

30:15.947 --> 30:17.396
No. No, of course not.

30:17.398 --> 30:18.898
Divya's pregnant.
She's not drinking.

30:18.900 --> 30:22.085
Evan, I've worked
all night, I...

30:22.087 --> 30:23.786
sorry, okay?
I'm so sorry.

30:23.788 --> 30:26.339
I made a terrible mistake.

30:26.341 --> 30:28.424
What mistake?

30:28.426 --> 30:29.742
- I thought that...
- What?

30:29.744 --> 30:32.712
[Static]
I thought... This... My surpr...

30:32.714 --> 30:34.597
what?
What do you mean, what?

30:34.599 --> 30:37.467
- What?
- I said I'm sorry.

30:37.469 --> 30:40.637
You don't sound sorry.
You sound annoyed.

30:40.639 --> 30:43.022
Look, why don't you call back

30:43.024 --> 30:44.257
when you have
a better connection?

30:44.259 --> 30:45.808
And you're sober.

30:45.810 --> 30:47.927
Paige, no, no, no.
I wasn't drink...

30:47.929 --> 30:49.095
Paige?

30:49.097 --> 30:51.948
[Whispers] Oh, my God.

30:58.939 --> 31:00.790
Henry, it's me.

31:00.792 --> 31:03.826
If you get this...

31:03.828 --> 31:06.412
I don't know, call.
I'm in Italy.

31:08.448 --> 31:10.800
Do you want to talk?

31:10.802 --> 31:14.587
Yeah,
but Hank's not picking up.

31:15.806 --> 31:19.592
You mean to you?

31:21.762 --> 31:24.564
No, it's fine.

31:24.566 --> 31:25.815
It will be fine.

31:25.817 --> 31:27.016
I just need to get home.

31:27.018 --> 31:30.970
Absolutely.
Let's go.

31:34.775 --> 31:36.526
[Car door closes]

31:37.778 --> 31:41.080
Okay.
[Engine sputters]

31:41.082 --> 31:43.449
[Sputtering]
What-

31:43.451 --> 31:45.985
you're kidding me.

31:45.987 --> 31:47.704
You're flooding it.
I'm not flooding it.

31:47.706 --> 31:50.373
Well, stop.
Okay, you're making it worse.

31:50.375 --> 31:51.507
I am not.

31:51.509 --> 31:52.875
Well,
you're not making it better!

31:52.877 --> 31:54.844
Well, neither are you,
you ninny!

31:54.846 --> 31:58.381
[Engine sputters]

32:02.102 --> 32:03.519
Sorry.

32:03.521 --> 32:05.504
I shouldn't be yelling at you.

32:05.506 --> 32:07.357
You're stressed,
you're not well.

32:07.359 --> 32:08.841
You called me a ninny.

32:08.843 --> 32:11.361
[Sighs]

32:11.363 --> 32:13.229
I'm stressed too.

32:13.231 --> 32:16.015
Why?
Why are you stressed?

32:16.017 --> 32:18.117
Your mom took the fact
you're having a baby so well.

32:18.119 --> 32:23.022
Yes, and all I have to do
is have a baby.

32:26.910 --> 32:30.997
Well, hold on a second.

32:30.999 --> 32:33.049
Are you worried
about being a mom?

32:33.051 --> 32:35.551
Of course not.

32:35.553 --> 32:37.337
A single woman having
her first child...

32:37.339 --> 32:39.722
what on earth do I have to be
worried about?

32:39.724 --> 32:41.841
I'm sorry, Divya.

32:41.843 --> 32:43.393
Ugh, I made this all about me.

32:43.395 --> 32:44.894
Um, okay.

32:44.896 --> 32:46.229
Do you want to talk about it?

32:46.231 --> 32:48.547
No. No, I just...
I want to fix this car

32:48.549 --> 32:51.267
and get you on that plane.
Right?

32:51.269 --> 32:54.270
Right.

32:54.272 --> 32:56.189
Okay, what's the diagnosis?

32:56.191 --> 32:58.724
No idea.

33:04.581 --> 33:06.366
[Exhales]

33:07.501 --> 33:09.619
How is it I can be

33:09.621 --> 33:12.588
in the most colossal
catastrophe ever,

33:12.590 --> 33:15.258
yet I'm less on edge
right now with you

33:15.260 --> 33:19.429
than I've been
all summer with...

33:19.431 --> 33:22.215
With Paige.

33:25.219 --> 33:30.023
I don't know, Evan.

33:30.025 --> 33:34.360
But I do know
that you thrive on drama.

33:34.362 --> 33:37.113
Excess, extremes.

33:37.115 --> 33:40.400
It's like good
is never good enough.

33:40.402 --> 33:45.822
You're married to a beautiful,
talented Saint of a woman.

33:45.824 --> 33:47.874
Your starter home is a castle.

33:47.876 --> 33:49.459
Relax and enjoy it.

33:49.461 --> 33:53.162
I know.
Look, everything should be good.

33:53.164 --> 33:54.914
Why is it so hard?

33:54.916 --> 33:58.835
It's like the two of us
are out of sync.

33:58.837 --> 34:00.586
Well, maybe...

34:00.588 --> 34:02.722
Maybe you expect
too much of her.

34:02.724 --> 34:06.592
What? I do not.

34:06.594 --> 34:08.293
Like what?

34:08.295 --> 34:10.263
Like a surprise party
in Tuscany?

34:10.264 --> 34:11.563
Where did that come from?

34:11.565 --> 34:13.599
Okay, no, no, no.
All right?

34:13.601 --> 34:15.735
She hinted and then you said...

34:15.737 --> 34:18.571
oh, Evan.

34:18.572 --> 34:21.824
It came from me.

34:21.826 --> 34:24.077
From my ninny skull.

34:24.079 --> 34:27.480
You have a need
for the grandiose.

34:27.482 --> 34:29.532
Right now I have
a need to get home

34:29.534 --> 34:31.451
and explain my mistake.

34:31.453 --> 34:33.286
I love Paige.
I love her so much.

34:33.288 --> 34:34.704
I would do anything for her.

34:34.706 --> 34:36.005
I'd do anything and everything!

34:36.007 --> 34:37.656
Well, nothing grandiose
about that.

34:37.658 --> 34:39.926
Yeah, see?

34:39.928 --> 34:42.011
Thank you.

34:43.297 --> 34:44.964
Yeah.

34:46.016 --> 34:48.167
Ooh.

34:48.168 --> 34:51.687
It's like we're out of sync.

34:51.688 --> 34:53.889
Why is it so hard?

34:53.891 --> 34:56.391
You're thinking
that sounds cliche.

34:56.393 --> 34:59.479
No, I'm thinking
the Van Der Gelts

34:59.481 --> 35:01.697
will never miss this Bordeaux.

35:01.699 --> 35:03.032
[Laughs]

35:03.034 --> 35:05.818
It is amazing.

35:07.321 --> 35:11.374
So what was
the real birthday plan?

35:11.376 --> 35:13.075
I was listening.

35:13.077 --> 35:14.527
A bit.

35:14.529 --> 35:16.829
Well, Evan and I
put ourselves on a budget,

35:16.831 --> 35:18.915
so I was thinking small.

35:18.917 --> 35:20.299
Of course it turns out

35:20.301 --> 35:21.884
he wanted
a private jet to Tuscany.

35:21.886 --> 35:23.219
Well, man are like that.

35:23.221 --> 35:25.087
They never tell you
what they want,

35:25.089 --> 35:28.758
then expect you
to read their minds.

35:28.760 --> 35:31.511
Of course, if you get it wrong,

35:31.513 --> 35:36.516
they get all emotional
and accuse you of not caring.

35:36.518 --> 35:38.651
Are you sure
you aren't thinking of women?

35:38.653 --> 35:40.553
Positive.
His name was Ralph.

35:40.555 --> 35:43.356
Ralph.

35:43.358 --> 35:45.057
Another time,
a different bottle.

35:45.059 --> 35:47.610
So your birthday plans
were small.

35:47.612 --> 35:49.779
But nostalgic.

35:49.781 --> 35:52.064
I read that the Jersey devil
on the boardwalk

35:52.066 --> 35:54.283
is shutting down.
The Jersey devil is-

35:54.285 --> 35:56.252
- a roller coaster
that scared Evan

35:56.254 --> 35:57.670
to death as a kid.

35:57.672 --> 36:00.456
So I booked it for a whole hour

36:00.458 --> 36:01.924
this afternoon.

36:01.926 --> 36:05.511
They even agreed to run it
a little slower if necessary

36:05.513 --> 36:07.746
so that Evan could get
that shot he always wanted.

36:07.748 --> 36:11.384
Hands up, fearless,
like all the other kids.

36:11.386 --> 36:15.555
That is so sweet.

36:15.557 --> 36:19.442
But it's not Tuscany.

36:19.444 --> 36:23.312
By the way,
my birthday is coming up.

36:23.314 --> 36:27.099
And I hear
they're shutting down Paris.

36:27.101 --> 36:29.952
[Laughs] [Glasses clink]

36:32.789 --> 36:35.441
<i>Santo padre, devo alta...</i>

36:35.443 --> 36:36.626
Evan, Evan, stop.

36:36.628 --> 36:38.461
Any of you kids speak English?

36:38.463 --> 36:41.130
Tell your father

36:41.132 --> 36:43.949
that we know that you're not
headed towards the airport,

36:43.951 --> 36:46.385
but if you could drop him off...

36:46.387 --> 36:51.507
[speaking italian]

36:51.509 --> 36:55.461
Ah.
<i>Quando e il suo volo?</i>

36:55.463 --> 36:57.179
What time is
your husband's plane?

36:57.181 --> 36:59.465
- No, no. We're not together.
- His flight is in an hour.

36:59.467 --> 37:02.635
We'll pay you whatever you need.
Okay.

37:02.637 --> 37:05.571
[Speaking italian]

37:05.573 --> 37:08.024
No, no, no, no.
No money. No money.

37:08.026 --> 37:11.744
[Speaking italian]

37:11.746 --> 37:13.412
If you can climb up the side,

37:13.414 --> 37:14.830
you can ride in back.

37:14.832 --> 37:15.948
- Really?
- Yeah.

37:15.950 --> 37:17.333
Oh,<i>grazie.</i>

37:17.335 --> 37:19.252
You are saving my life.

37:19.254 --> 37:20.503
<i>Tu mi hai...</i>

37:20.505 --> 37:22.421
<i>Riempito di conservanti!</i>

37:22.423 --> 37:23.656
<i>- Conservanti.</i>
<i>- Si?</i> Okay, great.

37:23.658 --> 37:25.675
Go, go.
Go out. Go out.

37:25.677 --> 37:27.826
Okay.
[Pigs oink]

37:27.828 --> 37:29.995
Okay.

37:29.997 --> 37:31.547
Okay.

37:31.549 --> 37:33.349
There are pigs in there.

37:33.351 --> 37:35.384
Yes.
There are good, good pigs.

37:35.386 --> 37:36.852
Very nice.

37:36.854 --> 37:39.055
Great.

37:39.057 --> 37:41.507
Papa will call the man
to come fix your car.

37:41.509 --> 37:42.841
<i>Grazie.</i>

37:42.843 --> 37:45.278
So, uh,

37:45.280 --> 37:46.729
I don't think I can do this.

37:46.731 --> 37:51.784
You said you could do
anything and everything.

37:51.786 --> 37:53.452
You're right.

37:53.454 --> 37:55.854
[Sighs]

37:57.074 --> 37:59.125
Oh, God.
Oh, my God.

37:59.127 --> 38:00.743
Oh, God.
Oh, my God.

38:00.745 --> 38:01.994
Oh, my God.

38:01.996 --> 38:04.547
Thank you, Divya,
for everything.

38:04.549 --> 38:05.581
[Father, indistinct]

38:05.583 --> 38:08.033
Okay.

38:09.670 --> 38:11.887
Okay, guys, so...

38:11.889 --> 38:14.390
Let's have an understanding
here.

38:14.392 --> 38:16.759
[Overlapping chatter]

38:16.761 --> 38:19.178
It's actually not that bad.
[Laughs] Great!

38:19.180 --> 38:21.897
[Father indistinct] Okay!

38:21.899 --> 38:23.549
[Laughs]
[Father speaking italian]

38:23.551 --> 38:25.050
<i>Ciao,</i> Italy!

38:25.052 --> 38:26.402
Paige, here I come!

38:26.404 --> 38:28.354
[Pigs squealing]
Ow! No biting! Ow!

38:28.356 --> 38:29.905
No! Stop biting!

38:29.907 --> 38:32.158
They're biting me!
Ow!

38:32.160 --> 38:34.126
Stop biting me!

39:44.688 --> 39:47.540
So tell me, what plans have
you made for your baby?

39:47.542 --> 39:49.292
None.

39:49.294 --> 39:52.178
I keep meaning to, but
every time I think about it,

39:52.180 --> 39:54.096
that part of my brain
goes all fuzzy.

39:54.098 --> 39:56.966
That's pregnancy.

39:56.968 --> 39:59.385
Pundit-ji always tells me
to live in the present.

39:59.387 --> 40:01.354
But the only time I could

40:01.356 --> 40:03.339
was when I was pregnant,

40:03.341 --> 40:05.674
especially with you.

40:05.676 --> 40:07.193
Why with me?

40:07.195 --> 40:10.363
You were the second,
so I wasn't as nervous.

40:10.365 --> 40:13.015
But I think
it was also about you.

40:13.017 --> 40:15.851
From the start,
I knew you were changing me

40:15.853 --> 40:17.737
for the better.

40:17.739 --> 40:20.957
You know, if you'd
said that to me before,

40:20.959 --> 40:24.377
I would have thought
that you were crazy.

40:24.379 --> 40:27.463
But now, it makes sense.

40:27.465 --> 40:31.133
Whoever this is,

40:31.135 --> 40:35.371
this baby,
makes me feel so different,

40:35.373 --> 40:40.560
so challenged,
and yet strangely content.

40:40.562 --> 40:44.480
It's like I know a secret.

40:44.482 --> 40:48.684
A really good secret.

40:48.686 --> 40:51.187
You're going to be
a wonderful mother, Divya.

40:59.279 --> 41:01.614
So when do you think
he'll be off the vent?

41:01.616 --> 41:02.999
With any luck, tomorrow.

41:03.001 --> 41:06.068
Soon after that, conscious.

41:06.070 --> 41:07.587
Pretty amazing save
you made, Dr. Lawson.

41:07.589 --> 41:09.338
Oh. Thanks.
I got lucky.

41:09.340 --> 41:13.042
- Get some rest.
- Will do.

41:34.031 --> 41:36.265
You're even working your magic
out on the north fork.

41:36.267 --> 41:38.367
No magic.
Just medicine.

41:38.369 --> 41:40.870
Molly's pretty upset.

41:40.872 --> 41:43.039
Yeah, well, it was
a pretty serious situation

41:43.041 --> 41:44.290
out there for both of them.

41:44.292 --> 41:45.491
Yeah.

41:48.611 --> 41:51.747
She's saying some pretty
serious things about you too.

41:51.749 --> 41:53.833
About me?

41:53.835 --> 41:55.668
She said you gave her
a narcotic

41:55.670 --> 41:58.004
that was prescribed to you.

41:58.006 --> 42:02.224
She also says that you've been
on those pills for a while.

42:02.226 --> 42:04.810
Hank, the police want you
to submit to a tox screen,

42:04.812 --> 42:08.064
and I told them that
wouldn't be a problem.

42:08.066 --> 42:10.599
